Package org.sbml.jsbml.ext.render.director

Class AbstractLayoutBuilder<P,NodeT,ArcT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.ext.render.director.AbstractLayoutBuilder<P,NodeT,ArcT>
  • Type Parameters:
    P -

    ArcT -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LayoutBuilder<P>, LayoutFactory<NodeT,ArcT>

    public abstract class AbstractLayoutBuilder<P,NodeT,ArcT>
extends java.lang.Object
implements LayoutBuilder<P>, LayoutFactory<NodeT,ArcT>
    This abstract class combines the interfaces LayoutBuilder and LayoutFactory. It implements the methods getSBGNNode(int), getSBGNArc(int) and getSBGNReactionNode(int) to get the node, arc or process node for a specific SBO term or a specific species reference role.
    Since:
    1.4
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger

        public SBGNArc<ArcT> createArc​(SpeciesReferenceGlyph srg,
                               ReactionGlyph reactionGlyph)
        Create a SBGNArc for the given SpeciesReferenceGlyph and ReactionGlyph. The decision which arc to produce is based on the role (priority) or the SBO term of the SpeciesReferenceGlyph.
        Parameters:
        srg - the SpeciesReferenceGlyph of the arc
        reactionGlyph - the ReactionGlyph of the arc
        Returns:
        a SBGNArc for the two given objects
